1
00:03:00,849 --> 00:03:02,267
Dad.

2
00:04:47,956 --> 00:04:52,210
Clear the ramp! 30 seconds!
God be with you!

3
00:04:52,293 --> 00:04:57,549
Port side stick, starboard side stick,
move fast and clear those murder holes.

4
00:04:57,632 --> 00:04:59,968
I want to see plenty of beach
between men.

5
00:05:00,051 --> 00:05:03,972
Five men is a juicy opportunity.
One man is a waste of ammo.

6
00:05:04,055 --> 00:05:06,140
Keep the sand out of your weapons.

7
00:05:06,266 --> 00:05:10,645
Keep those actions clear.
And I'll see you on the beach.

8
00:05:34,800 --> 00:05:41,800
FarangSiam thanks you. Enjoy!

9
00:05:42,802 --> 00:05:45,013
«Clear the mortar holes!»

10
00:06:01,362 --> 00:06:02,906
Over the side!

11
00:06:09,412 --> 00:06:11,831
«Port and starboard, over...»

12
00:07:21,025 --> 00:07:22,276
Jesus.

13
00:07:22,735 --> 00:07:24,487
Thank you...

14
00:09:43,376 --> 00:09:46,420
I said, what the hell do we do now, sir?

15
00:09:47,880 --> 00:09:51,092
«Captain Miller! Captain Miller!»

16
00:09:52,718 --> 00:09:55,888
- Captain Miller!
- Sergeant Horvath!

17
00:09:57,473 --> 00:10:01,144
Move your men off the beach! Go!

18
00:10:01,227 --> 00:10:02,562
Okay, you guys!

19
00:10:02,645 --> 00:10:05,731
- Get on my ass! Follow me!
- Sir!

20
00:10:06,107 --> 00:10:08,109
What's the rallying point?

21
00:10:08,234 --> 00:10:10,027
Anywhere but here!

22
00:10:23,082 --> 00:10:25,585
The seawall! Move up to the seawall!

23
00:10:25,668 --> 00:10:27,962
Sir, I'm staying!

24
00:10:28,045 --> 00:10:30,339
Clear this beach!
Make way for the others!

25
00:10:30,423 --> 00:10:33,009
This is all we got
between us and the Almighty.

26
00:10:33,092 --> 00:10:37,096
Every inch of this beach
has been pre-sighted!

27
00:10:38,014 --> 00:10:41,309
You stay here, you're dead men!

28
00:10:54,530 --> 00:10:58,075
Mama! Mama!

29
00:11:02,705 --> 00:11:05,208
«Stay down! Stay down!»

30
00:11:09,879 --> 00:11:11,214
What are you guys?

31
00:11:11,297 --> 00:11:14,008
104th Medical Battalion, sir!

32
00:11:14,091 --> 00:11:16,761
Here to set up field operations!

33
00:11:16,844 --> 00:11:18,387
Get rid of that crap!

34
00:11:18,471 --> 00:11:21,557
Grab yourselves some weapons.
Follow me.

35
00:11:29,148 --> 00:11:32,068
«- I'm hit! I'm hit!»
- Briggs!

36
00:11:36,322 --> 00:11:40,576
Get me out of here. I'm hit low. God!

37
00:11:40,660 --> 00:11:43,746
- Medic!
- Navy Beach Battalion, sir.

38
00:11:43,829 --> 00:11:47,583
I gotta clear these obstacles,
make holes for the tanks.

39
00:11:47,667 --> 00:11:50,002
All the armor is foundering
in the Channel.

40
00:11:50,086 --> 00:11:53,339
Orders, sir. You go somewhere else.
I'm clearing this one!

41
00:11:53,422 --> 00:11:55,174
Come on, Briggs!

42
00:11:59,804 --> 00:12:01,180
Medic!

43
00:12:38,259 --> 00:12:39,885
«Move! Move!»

44
00:12:47,560 --> 00:12:50,688
«Move! Come on! Move!»

45
00:13:12,460 --> 00:13:15,796
Shore party.
No armor has made it ashore.

46
00:13:15,880 --> 00:13:20,593
We got no DD tanks on the beach.
Dog One is not open.

47
00:13:21,552 --> 00:13:25,181
- Who's in command here?
- You are, sir!

48
00:13:26,807 --> 00:13:29,268
- Sergeant Horvath!
- Sir!

49
00:13:29,352 --> 00:13:31,395
You recognize where we are?

50
00:13:31,479 --> 00:13:33,898
Right where we're supposed to be,
but no one else is!

51
00:13:33,981 --> 00:13:37,443
Nobody's where they're supposed to be.

52
00:13:37,526 --> 00:13:39,111
Shore party.

53
00:13:39,904 --> 00:13:42,156
First wave, ineffective.

54
00:13:42,239 --> 00:13:46,285
We do not hold the beach.
Say again, we do not hold the beach.

55
00:13:46,660 --> 00:13:48,037
We're all mixed up, sir.

56
00:13:48,120 --> 00:13:49,914
We got the leftovers from Fox Company,

57
00:13:49,997 --> 00:13:51,957
Able Company and George Company!

58
00:13:52,041 --> 00:13:55,669
Plus we got some Navy demo guys
and a beachmaster!

59
00:13:57,213 --> 00:14:00,216
Shore party. Shore party.

60
00:14:06,305 --> 00:14:08,641
CATF, CATF...

61
00:14:12,144 --> 00:14:14,438
- Reiben here, sir!
- Did you see anybody else?

62
00:14:14,522 --> 00:14:17,316
- Jackson, but that's about it.
- Mellish here.

63
00:14:17,400 --> 00:14:20,653
Caparzo! We got DeForest
back there with Wade.

64
00:14:20,736 --> 00:14:24,490
He's hurt so bad he says
he sprung 100 leaks.

65
00:14:24,573 --> 00:14:26,242
Wade says he's all used up.

66
00:14:26,325 --> 00:14:28,577
- Move on to somebody you can help.
- Let's go!

67
00:14:28,661 --> 00:14:31,122
He's battalion surgeon, sir!

68
00:14:35,167 --> 00:14:37,128
- Get his attention.
- Wade!

69
00:14:37,211 --> 00:14:38,712
- Yo, Doc!
- Wade!

70
00:14:38,796 --> 00:14:41,966
- Wade! Wade! Wade!
- Wade!

71
00:14:43,008 --> 00:14:46,303
- Wade! Wade! Wade!
- Too risky, Doc. Too risky.

72
00:14:47,763 --> 00:14:49,849
- Wade!
- All right. Get him off the beach.

73
00:14:49,932 --> 00:14:53,686
I got it! We stopped the bleeding!
We stopped the bleeding!

74
00:14:55,229 --> 00:14:56,856
Fuck!

75
00:14:56,939 --> 00:15:00,234
Just give us a fucking chance,
you son of a bitch!

76
00:15:00,317 --> 00:15:02,736
- Son of a fucking cocksucker!
- Wade! Come on. Come on.

77
00:15:02,820 --> 00:15:06,031
«Wade! It's Mellish! Wade!»

78
00:15:06,574 --> 00:15:08,242
«- Mellish!
- Let's go!»

79
00:15:08,325 --> 00:15:09,493
«We found Miller!»

80
00:15:09,577 --> 00:15:12,163
«- Fuck it!
- Let's move! Let's move!»

81
00:15:19,211 --> 00:15:22,339
This is all? This is all that's made it?

82
00:15:22,423 --> 00:15:25,926
We got scattered pretty bad, sir.
There's bound to be more.

83
00:15:26,927 --> 00:15:29,263
- Not enough. It's not enough.
- Dog One exit...

84
00:15:29,346 --> 00:15:30,912
It's gotta be that cut on the right.

85
00:15:31,012 --> 00:15:33,309
- Or is that one on the left? Shit!
- No. No, no, no.

86
00:15:33,392 --> 00:15:36,103
Vierville is to the west of us.
This is Dog One.

87
00:15:36,187 --> 00:15:37,438
They're killing us!

88
00:15:37,521 --> 00:15:41,650
And we don't have a fucking chance,
and that ain't fair!

89
00:15:41,734 --> 00:15:44,111
Gather weapons and ammo!

90
00:15:44,195 --> 00:15:46,030
Gather weapons and ammo!

91
00:15:46,113 --> 00:15:49,200
Come on, let's drag them in
off the sand!

92
00:15:57,291 --> 00:16:01,212
Reiben. Hey, Reiben, Reiben, Reiben,
where's your BAR?

93
00:16:01,962 --> 00:16:04,354
Bottom of the channel, sir.
The bitch tried to drown me.

94
00:16:04,454 --> 00:16:06,331
Find a replacement.

95
00:16:08,093 --> 00:16:11,055
Bangalores! Bring up some bangalores!

96
00:16:12,431 --> 00:16:16,018
«Grenades, grenades! Get me
some grenades. Get them over here!»

97
00:16:18,687 --> 00:16:22,691
Bangalores up the line!
Bangalores up the line!

98
00:16:22,775 --> 00:16:25,027
Heads up! Bangers coming your way!

99
00:16:25,110 --> 00:16:27,530
Come on, come on, come on!

100
00:16:27,613 --> 00:16:30,449
- Jackson here, sir!
- Reiben back, sir!

101
00:16:31,116 --> 00:16:33,911
Oh, my God!

102
00:16:36,914 --> 00:16:39,375
One more. Give me one more.

103
00:16:44,713 --> 00:16:47,383
Oh, my God, it hurts! I'm gonna die!

104
00:16:47,466 --> 00:16:51,470
Oh, my God! Oh, Jesus! Oh, my God!

105
00:16:52,596 --> 00:16:55,975
Keep it moving. Keep it moving.
Almost got it.

106
00:16:56,100 --> 00:16:59,144
- Jesus! Lucky bastard.
- Come on.

107
00:16:59,979 --> 00:17:02,314
- Move it!
- Keep it moving. You got it?

108
00:17:02,398 --> 00:17:05,442
God! God, help me!

109
00:17:06,068 --> 00:17:07,987
You're not gonna die.
You're not gonna die.

110
00:17:08,070 --> 00:17:11,240
You're fine. Don't look at it.
Don't look at it.

111
00:17:11,323 --> 00:17:15,077
Bangalores! Clear the shingle!

112
00:17:15,160 --> 00:17:17,830
- Fire in the hole!
- Fire in the hole!

113
00:17:17,913 --> 00:17:20,457
Fire in the hole!

114
00:17:21,625 --> 00:17:23,335
Fire in the hole!

115
00:17:32,970 --> 00:17:36,682
We're in business! Defilade!
Other side of the hole!

116
00:17:49,737 --> 00:17:52,031
That's it! Let's go!

117
00:17:55,534 --> 00:17:57,661
Inspected. Morphine.

118
00:18:00,539 --> 00:18:01,874
Routine.

119
00:18:07,921 --> 00:18:09,381
Priority.

120
00:18:13,385 --> 00:18:14,595
He's gone.

121
00:18:27,024 --> 00:18:28,734
Son of a...

122
00:18:29,526 --> 00:18:32,196
- Get in there.
- Fuck. I can't move.

123
00:18:32,279 --> 00:18:33,489
- Mellish.
- Yes, sir.

124
00:18:33,572 --> 00:18:35,407
Give me your bayonet.

125
00:18:55,636 --> 00:18:59,390
Two MG42s and two mortars.
Add 20, left 30.

126
00:19:02,076 --> 00:19:05,229
There's a little defilade over there,
but it's the perfect fire position

127
00:19:05,312 --> 00:19:07,095
if we get some goddamn armor
on the beach.

128
00:19:07,195 --> 00:19:10,192
We gotta open up this draw!
We gotta get this draw open.

129
00:19:10,275 --> 00:19:12,194
Reiben, Mellish, let's get into the war!

130
00:19:12,277 --> 00:19:15,280
Grab some cover
and put some fire on that crew.

131
00:19:15,406 --> 00:19:19,118
Davis, Debernardo,
Young, Valk, get ready.

132
00:19:21,453 --> 00:19:23,122
Covering fire!

133
00:19:26,500 --> 00:19:28,210
Go, go, go!

134
00:19:42,224 --> 00:19:44,184
Goddamn firing squad.

135
00:19:44,309 --> 00:19:47,479
It's the only way we can get
everybody the hell out of here.

136
00:19:47,563 --> 00:19:51,775
Short, Payton, McDonald, Parkes!
You're next!

137
00:19:51,859 --> 00:19:54,486
Why don't we just hand out
blindfolds, Cap?

138
00:19:54,570 --> 00:19:56,155
All we can do here is die.

139
00:19:56,238 --> 00:19:57,823
Covering fire!

140
00:20:00,325 --> 00:20:02,077
Go, go, go!

141
00:20:03,328 --> 00:20:05,038
Come on! Come on! Come on!

142
00:20:05,164 --> 00:20:06,999
Go, God damn it!

143
00:20:19,386 --> 00:20:22,055
- Jackson.
- Sir.

144
00:20:22,965 --> 00:20:24,850
- Do you see that impact crater?
- Yes, sir.

145
00:20:24,933 --> 00:20:28,011
That should give you complete defilade
from that machine-gun position.

146
00:20:28,020 --> 00:20:29,977
Get in there and give me
some fire discipline.

147
00:20:29,980 --> 00:20:31,899
Wait for my command.

148
00:20:37,029 --> 00:20:38,405
Go!

149
00:20:49,458 --> 00:20:52,753
Captain, if your mother saw you do that,
she'd be very upset.

150
00:20:52,878 --> 00:20:55,130
I thought you were my mother.

151
00:20:55,964 --> 00:20:58,717
Be not thou far from me, O Lord.

152
00:21:03,263 --> 00:21:07,267
O my God, I am heartily sorry
for having offended thee.

153
00:21:08,477 --> 00:21:10,729
I detest my sins
for having offended thee, O Lord.

154
00:21:10,813 --> 00:21:12,944
I detest my sins for having
offended thee, O Lord.

155
00:21:13,044 --> 00:21:15,088
Listen to me, Lord.

156
00:21:19,738 --> 00:21:23,325
All my strength, haste thee to help me.

157
00:21:39,091 --> 00:21:44,137
- Dog One exit! Right here!
- We're in business!

158
00:21:45,681 --> 00:21:47,516
Move! Move!

159
00:22:28,807 --> 00:22:30,475
- Reiben.
- Let's go, Sarge. Go!

160
00:22:30,559 --> 00:22:31,852
Reiben.

161
00:22:56,668 --> 00:22:59,171
The place is full of 'em!

162
00:23:00,714 --> 00:23:02,341
Come on, Doyle!

163
00:23:03,842 --> 00:23:05,302
Sarge?

164
00:23:10,641 --> 00:23:13,685
- Flame!
- Doyle, do it!

165
00:23:18,231 --> 00:23:20,901
Don't shoot! Let them burn!

166
00:23:42,881 --> 00:23:46,176
I'll give you <comrade>,
you son of a bitch!

167
00:23:46,259 --> 00:23:47,886
Lie down!

168
00:24:16,123 --> 00:24:18,583
Cease fire! Cease fire!

169
00:24:18,709 --> 00:24:21,878
Cut it out! Cut it out! Cease fire!

170
00:24:22,921 --> 00:24:24,631
Sugar Cane. Sugar Charlie 3.

171
00:24:24,756 --> 00:24:27,968
Say again, Dog One is open.
Send in the dozers.

172
00:24:28,093 --> 00:24:31,096
I'm waiting for you
to tie in my flanks. Over.

173
00:24:32,139 --> 00:24:33,598
What?

174
00:24:36,226 --> 00:24:39,563
What? I'm sorry, I can't understand
what you're saying.

175
00:24:47,487 --> 00:24:50,032
What did he say? What did he say?

176
00:24:50,115 --> 00:24:53,326
"Look, I washed for supper."

177
00:24:57,956 --> 00:24:59,458
God damn it!

178
00:25:05,839 --> 00:25:07,424
- Hey, Fish.
- Yeah?

179
00:25:07,507 --> 00:25:10,177
Look at this. A Hitler Youth knife.

180
00:25:11,678 --> 00:25:14,848
And now
it's a Shabbat challah cutter, right?

181
00:25:24,775 --> 00:25:26,443
«Keep it moving!»

182
00:26:26,628 --> 00:26:28,505
«That's quite a view.»

183
00:26:29,464 --> 00:26:31,007
Yes, it is.

184
00:26:32,717 --> 00:26:34,261
Quite a view.

185
00:28:09,064 --> 00:28:11,233
«Dear Mr. Brian Boyd,»

186
00:28:11,250 --> 00:28:13,619
«no doubt by now you have
received full information...»

187
00:28:13,620 --> 00:28:16,131
«- Dear Mrs. Jensen...»
«- ...untimely death of your son.»

188
00:28:16,135 --> 00:28:18,309
«...no words of mine
can ever relieve the grief...»

189
00:28:18,315 --> 00:28:20,237
«Our outfit has felt his loss
tremendously.»

190
00:28:20,242 --> 00:28:22,994
«He was a fine soldier
and he believed very strongly in...»

191
00:28:23,078 --> 00:28:25,789
«It's no secret anymore
that we were involved»

192
00:28:25,872 --> 00:28:28,177
«in one of the most important
operations of this war.»

193
00:28:28,277 --> 00:28:30,585
«Al was the one
who held us all together.»

194
00:28:30,590 --> 00:28:32,341
«He was always the
first to volunteer...»

195
00:28:32,345 --> 00:28:35,674
«...came to a clearing near a road
where over 4,000 troops had passed...»

196
00:28:35,715 --> 00:28:37,926
«Your husband served in a combat unit»

197
00:28:38,009 --> 00:28:40,553
«whose dangerous duty
is to place itself...»

198
00:28:40,637 --> 00:28:43,765
«... which we all cherish
and hold so dear.»

199
00:28:43,848 --> 00:28:47,560
«The loss of Lee and others like him
is a distinct blow to the regiment.»

200
00:28:47,644 --> 00:28:49,036
«I fully understand your desire»

201
00:28:49,136 --> 00:28:51,690
«to learn as much as possible
regarding the circumstances»

202
00:28:51,773 --> 00:28:53,900
«leading to his death.»

203
00:29:46,077 --> 00:29:48,208
Colonel, I've got something
you should know about.

204
00:29:48,308 --> 00:29:49,601
Yes.

205
00:29:51,207 --> 00:29:53,752
These two men died in Normandy.

206
00:29:54,377 --> 00:29:57,213
This one at Omaha Beach.

207
00:29:57,297 --> 00:30:00,759
- Sean Ryan.
- This man at Utah.

208
00:30:02,427 --> 00:30:04,137
Peter Ryan.

209
00:30:07,891 --> 00:30:10,977
This man was killed
last week in New Guinea.

210
00:30:13,730 --> 00:30:16,149
Daniel Ryan.

211
00:30:16,858 --> 00:30:18,777
The three men are brothers, sir.

212
00:30:18,860 --> 00:30:20,556
I've just learned that, this afternoon,

213
00:30:20,656 --> 00:30:24,452
their mother is going
to be getting all three telegrams.

214
00:30:27,160 --> 00:30:29,508
That's not all. There's a
fourth brother. The youngest.

215
00:30:29,608 --> 00:30:31,498
He parachuted in
with the 101st Airborne,

216
00:30:31,581 --> 00:30:33,041
night before the invasion.

217
00:30:33,124 --> 00:30:35,168
He's somewhere in Normandy.
We don't know where.

218
00:30:35,268 --> 00:30:37,687
- Is he alive?
- We don't know.

219
00:30:41,633 --> 00:30:43,259
Come with me.

220
00:32:27,071 --> 00:32:29,449
«God damn it.»

221
00:32:30,283 --> 00:32:32,118
All four of them
were in the same company

222
00:32:32,202 --> 00:32:34,204
in the 29th Division,
but we split them up

223
00:32:34,287 --> 00:32:36,287
after the Sullivan brothers died
on the Juneau.

224
00:32:36,387 --> 00:32:39,918
Any contact with the fourth son, James?

225
00:32:40,001 --> 00:32:43,963
No, sir. He was dropped about
15 miles inland near Neuville.

226
00:32:44,047 --> 00:32:45,830
But that's still deep
behind German lines.

227
00:32:45,930 --> 00:32:47,634
Now, Mac,
there is no way you can know

228
00:32:47,717 --> 00:32:50,637
where in the hell he was dropped.

229
00:32:50,720 --> 00:32:52,894
General, first reports out of
Ike's people at SHAEF

230
00:32:52,978 --> 00:32:55,065
said the 101st is scattered
all to hell and gone.

231
00:32:55,165 --> 00:32:57,101
There's misdrops all over Normandy.

232
00:32:57,185 --> 00:33:00,104
Now, assuming Private Ryan
even survived the jump,

233
00:33:00,188 --> 00:33:01,648
he could be anywhere.

234
00:33:01,731 --> 00:33:03,775
In fact, he's probably KIA.

235
00:33:03,858 --> 00:33:07,529
And frankly, sir, we go sending
some sort of rescue mission,

236
00:33:07,612 --> 00:33:10,198
flathatting throughout swarms
of German reinforcements

237
00:33:10,281 --> 00:33:14,118
all along our axis of advance,
they're gonna be KIA, too.

238
00:33:36,641 --> 00:33:38,685
I have a letter here,

239
00:33:40,061 --> 00:33:44,148
written a long time ago
to a Mrs. Bixby in Boston.

240
00:33:44,232 --> 00:33:46,150
So bear with me.

241
00:33:48,987 --> 00:33:50,530
"Dear Madam,"

242
00:33:51,186 --> 00:33:53,491
"I have been shown in the files
of the War Department"

243
00:33:53,575 --> 00:33:57,328
"a statement of the Adjutant
General of Massachusetts"

244
00:33:57,412 --> 00:34:00,748
"that you are the mother of five"

245
00:34:03,751 --> 00:34:07,463
"sons who have died gloriously
on the field of battle."

246
00:34:10,133 --> 00:34:13,886
"I feel how weak and fruitless
must be any words of mine"

247
00:34:14,679 --> 00:34:18,057
"that would attempt
