"And then one day, you left."

1458
02:01:02,381 --> 02:01:06,385
"You left me, and I've been
desperate ever since."

1459
02:01:06,469 --> 02:01:09,639
"I see you all over the sky,
I see you all over the Earth."

1460
02:01:09,722 --> 02:01:11,390
Jesus, Upham,
any more songs like this,

1461
02:01:11,474 --> 02:01:13,344
the krauts aren't going
to have to shoot me.

1462
02:01:13,444 --> 02:01:16,103
I'm just going to slit my own wrists.

1463
02:01:16,229 --> 02:01:18,898
You know,
you're a strange bird, Upham.

1464
02:01:18,981 --> 02:01:20,858
Sorry, it's Edith, you know.

1465
02:01:20,942 --> 02:01:22,944
You know what
that song reminds me of?

1466
02:01:23,069 --> 02:01:25,765
It reminds me of Mrs. Rachel Troubowitz
and what she said to me

1467
02:01:25,865 --> 02:01:27,323
the day I left for basic.

1468
02:01:27,406 --> 02:01:29,951
What, "Don't touch me"?

1469
02:01:30,076 --> 02:01:32,620
