Sarge! Mike, are you all right?

1637
02:29:54,529 --> 02:29:57,312
- I just got the wind knocked out of me.
- Well, get out of here!

1638
02:29:57,412 --> 02:30:00,833
Take cover!
We're going to blow this bridge!

1639
02:30:01,953 --> 02:30:03,746
Come on, come on!

1640
02:30:08,543 --> 02:30:11,379
Tiger coming coming across the bridge!

1641
02:30:43,452 --> 02:30:46,706
Captain, get behind something!

1642
02:30:46,789 --> 02:30:49,458
«Come on, Captain, move it!»

1643
02:31:12,440 --> 02:31:13,649
Mike.

1644
02:31:18,821 --> 02:31:20,156
Mike!

1645
02:31:59,195 --> 02:32:00,488
«Captain.»

1646
02:32:03,240 --> 02:32:07,370
Captain, where the hell are you going?
Captain, get back here!

1647
02:34:00,441 --> 02:34:01,776
Upham.

1648
02:34:32,723 --> 02:34:34,975
Hang in there, Captain.

1649
02:35:19,061 --> 02:35:20,771
Medic!

1650
02:35:23,566 --> 02:35:26,110
Medic! We got a medic?

1651
02:35:32,908 --> 02:35:35,786
They're tank-busters, sir. P-51s.

1652
02:35:36,745 --> 02:35:38,956
Angels on our shoulders.

1653
02:35:44,920 --> 02:35:46,630
What, sir?

1654
02:35:51,093 --> 02:35:52,469
James...

1655
02:35:54,263 --> 02:35:55,764
Earn this.

1656
02:36:00,060 --> 02:36:01,478
Earn it.

1657
02:36:30,966 --> 02:36:33,135
«My dear Mrs. Ryan,»

1658
02:36:34,386 --> 02:36:36,847
«it's with the most
profound sense of joy»

1659
02:36:36,931 --> 02:36:42,102
«that I write to inform you
your son Private James Ryan»

1660
02:36:42,186 --> 02:36:44,313
«is well and, at this very moment,»

1661
02:36:44,396 --> 02:36:47,858
«on his way home
from European battlefields.»

1662
02:36:47,942 --> 02:36:51,445
«Reports from the front indicate
James did his duty in combat»

1663
02:36:51,528 --> 02:36:55,074
«with great courage
and steadfast dedication,»

1664
02:36:55,741 --> 02:36:58,327
«even after he was informed
of the tragic loss»

1665
02:36:58,410 --> 02:37:01,914
«your family has suffered
in this great campaign»

1666
02:37:01,997 --> 02:37:05,417
«to rid the world
of tyranny and oppression.»

1667
02:37:05,501 --> 02:37:08,754
«I take great pleasure in joining
the Secretary of War,»

1668
02:37:08,879 --> 02:37:11,006
«the men and women
of the United States Army»

1669
02:37:11,090 --> 02:37:13,467
«and the citizens of a grateful nation»

1670
02:37:13,550 --> 02:37:16,470
«in wishing you good health
and many years of happiness»

1671
02:37:16,553 --> 02:37:19,098
«with James at your side.»

1672
02:37:20,265 --> 02:37:24,269
«Nothing, not even the safe
return of a beloved son,»

1673
02:37:24,353 --> 02:37:25,896
«can compensate you»

1674
02:37:25,980 --> 02:37:29,024
«or the thousands
of other American families»

1675
02:37:29,108 --> 02:37:32,486
«who have suffered great loss
in this tragic war.»

1676
02:37:32,569 --> 02:37:36,073
«And I might share with you some words
which have sustained me»

1677
02:37:36,156 --> 02:37:40,285
«through long, dark nights of peril,
loss and heartache.»

1678
02:37:40,369 --> 02:37:41,829
«And I quote,»

1679
02:37:43,163 --> 02:37:44,748
«'I pray that our heavenly father»

1680
02:37:44,832 --> 02:37:48,043
«'may assuage the anguish
of your bereavement»

1681
02:37:48,127 --> 02:37:50,087
«'and leave you only
the cherished memory»

1682
02:37:50,170 --> 02:37:52,172
«'of the loved and lost»

1683
02:37:52,256 --> 02:37:54,633
«'and the solemn pride
that must be yours»

1684
02:37:54,717 --> 02:37:59,471
«'to have laid so costly a sacrifice
upon the altar of freedom.»

1685
02:38:00,222 --> 02:38:01,890
«'Abraham Lincoln. '»

1686
02:38:02,433 --> 02:38:04,893
«Yours very sincerely and respectfully.»

1687
02:38:04,977 --> 02:38:08,272
«George C Marshall,
General, Chief of Staff.»

1688
02:38:59,698 --> 02:39:02,034
My family is with me today.

1689
02:39:02,951 --> 02:39:05,788
They wanted to come with me.

1690
02:39:07,456 --> 02:39:08,624
To be honest with you,

1691
02:39:08,707 --> 02:39:11,960
I wasn't sure how I'd feel
coming back here.

1692
02:39:15,339 --> 02:39:18,801
Every day I think about
what you said to me

1693
02:39:18,884 --> 02:39:20,969
that day on the bridge.

1694
02:39:22,888 --> 02:39:26,308
And I've tried to live my life
the best I could.

1695
02:39:27,434 --> 02:39:29,812
I hope that was enough.

1696
02:39:30,604 --> 02:39:33,315
I hope that, at least in your eyes,

1697
02:39:35,150 --> 02:39:38,862
I've earned what all of you
have done for me.

1698
02:39:52,417 --> 02:39:53,752
James.

1699
02:39:56,004 --> 02:39:58,006
"Captain John H. Miller."

1700
02:40:06,682 --> 02:40:10,602
- Tell me I've led a good life.
- What?

1701
02:40:11,854 --> 02:40:14,022
Tell me I'm a good man.

1702
02:40:21,280 --> 02:40:22,865
You are.

